r-wear-os-app-satisfy-google-play-app-quality-requirements-a4f061f18e26?source=rss----95b274b437c2---4">tools and libraries you can use to help your Wear OS app satisfy Google Play app quality requirements</a>.</p><p><a href="https://medium.com/androiddevelopers/tools-and-libraries-to-help-your-wear-os-app-satisfy-google-play-app-quality-requirements-a4f061f18e26">Tools and libraries to help your Wear OS app satisfy Google Play app quality requirements</a></p><h3>Codelabs üõ†Ô∏è</h3><p>We‚Äôve also added new codelabs, check out the new pathway: <a href="https://developer.android.com/courses/pathways/improve-user-experience">Improve the user experience of an Android app</a>. Learn how Edge to Edge, Predictive Back, and Glance can enhance the user experience and quality of an Android¬†app.</p><p>Also, check out <a href="https://developer.android.com/codelabs/jetpack-compose-performance#0">Practical performance problem solving in Jetpack Compose</a>. In this codelab, you learn how to improve the runtime performance of a Compose¬†app.</p><h3><a href="http://adbackstage.libsyn.com/episode-206-make-it-faster">Android Developers Backstage</a>üéôÔ∏è</h3><p>On <a href="https://adbackstage.libsyn.com/episode-206-make-it-faster">Android Developers Backstage episode 206: ‚ÄúMake it faster‚Äù</a> we cover ADB, ‚ÄúAndroid Debug Bridge‚Äù, the technology powering device connections.</p><p>Romain and Tor talk with Fabien from the Android Studio team on his work to improve the debug stack‚Ää‚Äî‚Ääincluding the new USB speed detection feature recently unveiled at Google¬†I/O.</p><p>Listen to it in <a href="https://adbackstage.libsyn.com/episode-206-make-it-faster">podcast</a> or <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=D1xPZagZdqk">youtube</a>¬†format.</p><iframe src="https://cdn.embedly.com/widgets/media.html?src=%2F%2Fhtml5-player.libsyn.com%2Fembed%2Fepisode%2Fid%2F31424717%2Fheight%2F90%2Ftheme%2Fcustom%2Fthumbnail%2Fyes%2Fdirection%2Fforward%2Frender-playlist%2Fno%2Fcustom-col